 {"actor":"mayor","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-01T19:07:34Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":2541,"issue_id":"bd-ppnp","new_value":"{\"assignee\":\"beads/polecats/obsidian\",\"status\":\"hooked\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"bd-ppnp\",\"title\":\"fix/database_integrity.go: SQLite recovery does not restore backup on getBdBinary() failure\",\"description\":\"In fix/database_integrity.go sqliteIntegrityRecovery (lines ~113-117), if getBdBinary() fails, the function returns the error but does NOT restore the backup. The database file has already been moved at line ~103. Compare with doltIntegrityRecovery (lines ~58-61) which correctly restores the backup on getBdBinary() failure.\\n\\nThis leaves users with no database file at the expected path if getBdBinary() fails during SQLite recovery.\\n\\nSuggested fix: Restore backupDB back to dbPath before returning the error, matching the Dolt recovery pattern.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"steve.yegge@gmail.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-01T18:11:38Z\",\"created_by\":\"beads/polecats/jasper\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-01T18:11:38Z\"}"}
