 {"actor":"mayor","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-01T19:07:42Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":2543,"issue_id":"bd-uz1x","new_value":"{\"assignee\":\"beads/polecats/quartz\",\"status\":\"hooked\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"bd-uz1x\",\"title\":\"Federation checks: hardcoded port 8080 and possible wrong PID file path\",\"description\":\"In federation.go:\\n\\n1. Line ~112: remotesAPIPort is hardcoded to 8080. If the user configured a different remotesapi port, the check reports the wrong port as inaccessible. The port should be read from config, similar to how the SQL server port is derived via doltserver.DefaultConfig.\\n\\n2. Line ~71: CheckFederationRemotesAPI looks for PID file at filepath.Join(doltPath, 'dolt-server.pid') (inside the dolt data directory), but the PID file is typically at filepath.Join(beadsDir, 'dolt-server.pid') as seen in gitignore.go line 42. Wrong path means the check incorrectly reports server as not running.\\n\\n3. No test coverage exists for any federation checks.\\n\\nSuggested fix: Read port from config. Fix PID file path. Add tests.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"steve.yegge@gmail.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-01T18:11:33Z\",\"created_by\":\"beads/polecats/jasper\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-01T18:11:33Z\"}"}
 {"actor":"mayor","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-01T19:07:42Z","event_type":"updated","id":2544,"issue_id":"bd-uz1x","new_value":"{\"description\":\"attached_molecule: bd-wisp-6lb5i\\nattached_formula: mol-polecat-work\\nattached_at: 2026-03-02T03:07:42Z\\ndispatched_by: mayor\\n\\nIn federation.go:\\n\\n1. Line ~112: remotesAPIPort is hardcoded to 8080. If the user configured a different remotesapi port, the check reports the wrong port as inaccessible. The port should be read from config, similar to how the SQL server port is derived via doltserver.DefaultConfig.\\n\\n2. Line ~71: CheckFederationRemotesAPI looks for PID file at filepath.Join(doltPath, 'dolt-server.pid') (inside the dolt data directory), but the PID file is typically at filepath.Join(beadsDir, 'dolt-server.pid') as seen in gitignore.go line 42. Wrong path means the check incorrectly reports server as not running.\\n\\n3. No test coverage exists for any federation checks.\\n\\nSuggested fix: Read port from config. Fix PID file path. Add tests.\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"bd-uz1x\",\"title\":\"Federation checks: hardcoded port 8080 and possible wrong PID file path\",\"description\":\"In federation.go:\\n\\n1. Line ~112: remotesAPIPort is hardcoded to 8080. If the user configured a different remotesapi port, the check reports the wrong port as inaccessible. The port should be read from config, similar to how the SQL server port is derived via doltserver.DefaultConfig.\\n\\n2. Line ~71: CheckFederationRemotesAPI looks for PID file at filepath.Join(doltPath, 'dolt-server.pid') (inside the dolt data directory), but the PID file is typically at filepath.Join(beadsDir, 'dolt-server.pid') as seen in gitignore.go line 42. Wrong path means the check incorrectly reports server as not running.\\n\\n3. No test coverage exists for any federation checks.\\n\\nSuggested fix: Read port from config. Fix PID file path. Add tests.\",\"status\":\"hooked\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"assignee\":\"beads/p