 {"actor":"mayor","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-01T19:08:11Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":2549,"issue_id":"bd-md2p","new_value":"{\"assignee\":\"beads/polecats/opal\",\"status\":\"hooked\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"bd-md2p\",\"title\":\"Relative path usage makes doctor checks fragile when run from subdirectories\",\"description\":\"Multiple check functions construct paths relative to cwd instead of accepting a path parameter or resolving the project root:\\n\\n1. gitignore.go line ~91: CheckGitignore uses filepath.Join('.beads', '.gitignore')\\n2. gitignore.go: CheckRedirectNotTracked, CheckLastTouchedNotTracked, FixRedirectTracking, FixLastTouchedTracking all use relative paths\\n3. claude.go lines ~111-112, 175-176, 222-223: isBeadsPluginInstalled, isMCPServerInstalled, hasClaudeHooks use filepath.Join('.claude', 'settings.json')\\n\\nIf bd doctor is run from a subdirectory of the project, these checks will look in the wrong location. In contrast, functions like CheckConfigValues correctly take an explicit repoPath parameter.\\n\\nSuggested fix: Accept a path parameter or resolve the project root internally, consistent with other checks.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"steve.yegge@gmail.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-01T18:11:16Z\",\"created_by\":\"beads/polecats/jasper\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-01T18:11:16Z\"}"}
